<br>
Pet goes to about 20% life, and i use about 40% mana just chain nuking char, FoT=to much aggro, havnt tried it with SoFB tho, ill give that a shot, but its easy to solo those enforcers and punishers.<br>
<br>
But i got BOV last(yay me!!) night, and havnt tried that yet. Im sure with BOV will be easier still. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sharkeyy>sharkeyy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://banners.steakandcheese.com/sncbutton.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/02 10:58:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: !</span><hr size=1> Chain petting or Grabbing a lot of agro using various instant clicks to Rogue pet kite via 62 water pet works very well in PoN.  I have been farming the silks from these spiders and sap from the trees for some tailoring stuffs. No idea on my range of gear so <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79972&resize=true">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...esize=true</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> is magelo... umm... yeah 1/2 good 1/2 ghetto...  <br>
<br>
<br>
Yaksa &quot;Pumpkin pie&quot; LoveCraft <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.drew.edu/cpetrey/wonka-youlose2.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://mailto:cpetrey@drew.edu">Master Yaksa LoveCraft</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->63 Mage Luclin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Member of Legacy of Sorrow</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sitting on the bed or lying wide awake<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->There're demons in my head and it's more than I can take<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->I think I'm on a roll but I think it's kinda weak<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Saying all I know is I gotta get away from</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 745<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 11:28:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: !</span><hr size=1> Tried a spider in PoN near the Graveyard.  I was very successful up to a point.  They seem to have about the same amount of hit points as a Sun Revenant in the Grey, but hit about 50% harder, meaning instead of reclaiming on the third root, I have to reclaim on the second one.<br>
<br>
I got the spider to about 20% hit points when I had a root break.  I could not channel a new pet while getting hit for 150-250 points in triples, so I was forced to zone.<br>
<br>
I would say that with a 65 earth pet, soloing non-summoners would be quite viable, as the pet has a negative resist modifier on its root spell, and the pet cons level 60.  Getting to level 65 and getting the spell is the hard part.  Otherwise, I would say that having a mag partner would be quite viable and safe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zellis>Zellis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(12/23/02 10:34:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: !</span><hr size=1> PoN Banshees and nettling wraiths are easy with 65 earth, exp is almost worth solo'ing there.  However group in pov/hoh &gt; any solo spot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lianadmagi>Lianad Magi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(1/4/03 5:56:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   fun zone</span><hr size=1> Well,<br>
<br>
I finally got sick of soloing in POD, so decided to try out PON.  Let me say that PON is now my perma camp solo spot at 62, well until I try at storms <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
At level 62, trees, spiders, ravens etc, all mobs around GY yield roughly 2.2% AA exp.  I was averaging roughly 22% aa exp each hour.  I'm sure others could get much more, but my gear sucks and I need to med a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway I usually set up camp north of GY on the wall near where a static blood raven spawns.  My method is simple aggro kiting, load up 61 air pet, equip it with muzzle, belt, fists, and give it burnout (no need for DS).  I get at max range for FBOT, fire off 2 FBOT run back to pet, sick pet, and just kite it around.  I've found I like air pet better than water pet just because I can kill al ot faster because 1 the stuns are huge aggro on mob, and 2 the stuns stop the mob from chasing me giving me time to stop and nuke again.  Usually pet ends up like 75% hp (which he regens in like 30 seconds), and I end up spending 40mana on the mob..  Pretty much completely safe with run3 or jboots, if you get an add just zone out...<br>
<br>
